\mathop {\lim }\limits_{x \to a} f(x) \ne L \iff 
\varepsilon  > 0
\delta  > 0
x \ne a
\left| {x - a} \right| < \delta 
 \left| {f(x) - L} \right| \ge \varepsilon 
\varepsilon
\varepsilon
\mathop {\lim }\limits_{x \to 2}\; (x + 3) \ne 4
\;\epsilon =1\;
|x+3-4|=|x-1|\ge 1\iff\begin{cases}x-1\ge 1\iff x\ge 2&,\;or\\{}\\x-1\le-1\iff x\le 0\end{cases}
